about.summary: A collection of functions to facilitate analysis of proteomic data from Olink, primarily NPX data that has been exported from Olink NPX Manager or MyData. The functions also work on QUANT data from Olink by log- transforming the QUANT data. The functions are focused on reading data, facilitating data wrangling and quality control analysis, performing statistical analysis and generating figures to visualize the results of the statistical analysis. The goal of this package is to help users extract biological insights from proteomic data run on the Olink platform.

name: r-olinkanalyze
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '3.0.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-olinkanalyze
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/OlinkAnalyze_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/OlinkAnalyze/OlinkAnalyze_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a9e871ba44fca43d99eaec086b182e0d9fbd3cdd3fee1c2c437d0a9c36daeecd

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base >=4.0.0
    - r-broom
    - r-car
    - r-dplyr
    - r-emmeans
    - r-forcats
    - r-generics
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggpubr
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-lme4
    - r-lmertest
    - r-magrittr
    - r-readxl
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base >=4.0.0
    - r-broom
    - r-car
    - r-dplyr
    - r-emmeans
    - r-forcats
    - r-generics
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggpubr
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-lme4
    - r-lmertest
    - r-magrittr
    - r-readxl
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('OlinkAnalyze')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('OlinkAnalyze')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=OlinkAnalyze
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: A collection of functions to facilitate analysis of proteomic data from Olink, primarily
    NPX data that has been exported from Olink NPX Manager or MyData. The functions
    also work on QUANT data from Olink by log- transforming the QUANT data. The functions
    are focused on reading data, facilitating data wrangling and quality control analysis,
    performing statistical analysis and generating figures to visualize the results
    of the statistical analysis. The goal of this package is to help users extract biological
    insights from proteomic data run on the Olink platform.
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - AskPascal
